The paper deals with image separation and its application in art investigation. The proposed method involves the use of X-ray scans and photographs, which are both image modalities. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of dictionary learning, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper's application in art investigation suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia sub-category (cs.MM).
